      <memberdef kind="function" id="xilskey__jtag_8h_1a2240f1d411f1eef6605ee6da1426c5ba" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>u32</type>
        <definition>u32 JtagAES_Check_Ultrascale</definition>
        <argsstring>(u32 *Crc, u8 MarginOption)</argsstring>
        <name>JtagAES_Check_Ultrascale</name>
        <param>
          <type>u32 *</type>
          <declname>Crc</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u8</type>
          <declname>MarginOption</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function verifies the AES key of Ultrascale&apos;s EFUSE with provided CRC value. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Crc</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to a 32 bit variable which holds the expected AES key&apos;s CRC. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MarginOption</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a variable which tells the margin option in which read operation to be performed.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns XST_FAILURE/XST_SUCCESS<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS - If CRC is correct</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE - If CRC is wrong</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>To verify AES key with provided CRC 256 bits need to be written with all ZEROS and last 32 bits with CRC. And then CTS word should be framed and read 9 rows. The keys are stored in 8 rows (20 to 27) but in UltraScale the device will read all 1s. On the 9th read (row 28), the CRC computation takes place. An extra read after the 9th read is required to read the computed CRC out (can use last row addr of 28 or row 0). The FPGA internally compares the computed CRC with the expected CRC loaded through the FUSE_KEY operation. If they match, then the expected CRC is read. If not, the FPGA will return all 1s. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
